import './App.css';

import React, { Component } from 'react'
import Navbar from './Components/Navbar';
import News from './Components/News';
import {
  BrowserRouter as Router,
  Routes,
  Route,
  Link
} from "react-router-dom";

export default class App extends Component {
  render() {
    return (

      <Router>
        <Navbar></Navbar>
       
       <Routes>

       <Route path='/general'>
        <News pagesize = {9} Category ="general"></News>
        </Route>

       <Route path="/business">
       <News pagesize = {9} Category ="business"></News>
       </Route>

       <Route path="/entertainment">
       <News pagesize = {9} Category ="entertainment"></News> 
       </Route>

       <Route path="/health">
        <News pagesize = {9} Category ="health"></News>
       </Route>

       <Route path="/sports">
        <News pagesize = {9} Category ="sports"></News>
       </Route>

       <Route path="/science">
       <News pagesize = {9} Category ="science"></News>
       </Route>

       <Route path="/technology">
        <News pagesize = {9} Category ="technology"></News>
       </Route>
       

     </Routes>

    </Router>
      
    )
  }
}
